rComments: Pretty reasonable guy - I personally didn't enjoy his lectures that much but he's a fair grader and gives thorough outlines of what to expect on tests/exams. Memorize 100 or so slides for the final exam and you're golden.
Dr. Ewald is an amazing professor. Very knowledgeable, down to earth, and there for students. I've learned so much in this 4th year seminar course. He is also a fair maker for assignments.

I took this course few years ago, and I can still say that he is one of the best professors I have ever met. Very informative and interesting course about Ancient Rome. His presentations are interactive with videos, pictures, etc. Fair maker too. Would take it again.
Attendance is not mandatory but is a plus. Clear syllabus and always willing to help. Interesting course material.

I have taken two classes with Prof. Ewald this year and greatly enjoyed both. I found him helpful, approachable, and reasonable and his lectures engaging. FAH207 was a good introduction, but I loved FAH313. I am prone to skipping but didn't miss a single class.
Very interesting lectures with video simulations that helped better understand what ancient temples looked like. Unfortunately, did not have time to cover all the material.

This class was very easy; for a third year class, it felt like a first year class. You could get away with just reading the textbook and viewing the powerpoint slides and still get a high mark. He was very nice and sometimes funny, but his lectures weren't all that interesting, but the course material was very good, if you read it on your own.
